 class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Eric_Horvitz&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://research.microsoft.com/en-us/people/horvitz/">"Eric Horvitz: Distinguished Scientist"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEric+Horvitz&amp;rft.btitle=Eric+Horvitz%3A+Distinguished+Scientist&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fresearch.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fpeople%2Fhorvitz%2F&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">Gershgorn, Dave. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://qz.com/973005/microsofts-new-head-of-research-has-spent-his-career-building-powerful-ai-and-making-sure-its-safe/">"Microsoft\xe2\x80\x99s new head of research has spent his career building powerful AI\xe2\x80\x94and making sure it\xe2\x80\x99s safe"</a>. <i>Quartz</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2017-08-25</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEric+Horvitz&amp;rft.atitle=Microsoft%E2%80%99s+new+head+of+research+has+spent+his+caree